com.ltsllc.miranda.clientinterface.basicclasses

Class Mergeable

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ltsllc.miranda.clientinterface.basicclasses.Mergeable
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MirandaObject

    public abstract class Mergeable
extends java.lang.Object
    An Object that can be merged with another object.

    Instances of this class implicitly have the notion of when they were last changed. When merging with another instance of this class, the more recent version should be used.

      • copyFrom

        public abstract void copyFrom(Mergeable mergeable)
        Copy all attributes from another instance.

        After invoking this method, this instance should be Object.equals(Object) equivalent to the object passed to it.

        The argument should be of the same class as this instance.

        Any subclasses should copy their attributes.

        Parameters:
        mergeable - Another non-null instance that this object should copy from. The object should be of the same type as this instance --- casting to the type of the receiver should work.
